The paper discusses the design of defenses against attacks on Internet systems, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also mentions the simulation of both the system and the adversary, which could fall under distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC) or social and information networks (cs.SI). The paper also discusses the design and implementation of a simulated adversary, which could fall under networking and internet architecture (cs.NI) or software engineering (cs.SE).
